---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
import NextStep from '../../components/NextStep.astro';

export const title = "New Jersey Dispensary Licensing Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="How to Open a Dispensary in New Jersey | NJ Cannabis License" 
  description="The complete 2026 guide to obtaining a cannabis retail license in New Jersey. Learn about the CRC application process, priority scoring, and local rules."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1588421357574-87938a86fa28?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
  stateName="New Jersey"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Opening a Dispensary in New Jersey</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Your step-by-step roadmap to the Garden State market</p>
    </div>

    <Callout title="A Rapidly Expanding Frontier" type="passion">
      New Jersey is currently one of the most exciting cannabis markets on the East Coast. With a dense population and a committed regulatory framework, the opportunity to build a high-impact brand here is massive. The complexity is high, but the rewards are historic!
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>State Regulatory Body</h2>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.nj.gov/cannabis/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">New Jersey Cannabis Regulatory Commission (CRC)</a> is the official agency responsible for licensing and regulating all cannabis businesses in the state.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>License Types in NJ</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Class 5 Retailer:</strong> Permits the purchase of cannabis from cultivators/manufacturers and sale to consumers.</li>
        <li><strong>Class 1 Cultivator:</strong> Standard large-scale growing operations.</li>
        <li><strong>Microbusiness:</strong> A specialized category for smaller, local NJ founders with restricted canopy size and employee counts.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The NJ Priority System</h2>
      <p>New Jersey prioritizes specific applicants to ensure social equity and local ownership:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Social Equity Applicants:</strong> Individuals from economically disadvantaged areas.</li>
        <li><strong>Diverse-Owned Businesses:</strong> Minority, Women, or Disabled-Veteran owned.</li>
        <li><strong>Impact Zone Businesses:</strong> Located in municipalities specifically hit by the war on drugs.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>NJ Authority Links</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.nj.gov/cannabis/resources/licensing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NJ CRC Licensing Resources</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.nj.gov/cannabis/resources/statutes-rules/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NJ Cannabis Statutes and Rules</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only. NJ regulations change frequently. Verify all requirements with the NJ CRC.</em></p>
    </section>

    <NextStep currentPath="/nj/licensing/" />
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
